#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:14
msgid ""
"Our character in our game will have health by defining the "
"[code]health[/code] variable. The higher the character's health, the "
"further away the player is from losing the game."
msgstr ""
"Karakter kita dalam permainan kita akan memiliki kesehatan dengan "
"mendefinisikan variabel [code]health[/code]. Semakin tinggi kesehatan "
"karakter, semakin jauh pemain dari kekalahan."

msgid ""
"Health that changes adds tension to the game, especially if the player is"
" fighting with low health! It's a resource that the player should manage "
"carefully."
msgstr ""
"Kesehatan yang berubah menambah ketegangan dalam permainan, terutama jika"
" pemain bertarung dengan kesehatan yang rendah! Ini adalah sumber daya "
"yang harus dikelola pemain dengan hati-hati."

msgid ""
"The character's health might get low if an enemy attacks them or they "
"fall into a hole."
msgstr ""
"Kesehatan karakter mungkin berkurang jika musuh menyerangnya atau "
"terjatuh ke dalam lubang."

msgid "We can create a function to represent damage in these cases."
msgstr "Kita dapat membuat fungsi untuk mewakili kerusakan dalam kasus ini."

#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:40
msgid "We pass the amount of damage the robot should take as a parameter."
msgstr ""
"Kita mengirimkan jumlah kerusakan yang harus diterima robot sebagai "
"parameter."

msgid "Line 2 subtracts [code]amount[/code] from [code]health[/code]."
msgstr ""
"Pada baris ke-2, nilai [code]amount[/code] dikurangkan dari "
"[code]health[/code]."

msgid ""
"Note the [code]-=[/code] syntax which achieves this. It's a shorthand we "
"often use."
msgstr ""
"Perhatikan sintaks [code]-=[/code] yang digunakan untuk melakukan hal "
"ini. Ini adalah bentuk singkat yang sering digunakan."

msgid ""
"You can also use a longer form. Both of these lines have the same effect."
" They both subtract the value of [code]amount[/code] from the "
"[code]health[/code] variable:"
msgstr ""
"Kamu juga bisa menggunakan bentuk yang lebih panjang. Kedua baris di "
"bawah ini memiliki efek yang sama, yaitu mengurangkan nilai "
"[code]amount[/code] dari variabel [code]health[/code]:"

msgid ""
"[code]health -= amount[/code]\n"
"[code]health = health - amount[/code]"
msgstr ""
"[code]health -= amount[/code]\n"
"[code]health = health - amount[/code]"

msgid ""
"You may notice that the health of the robot can go below [code]0[/code]. "
"We'll see how to manage this in a future lesson using [i]conditions[/i]."
msgstr ""
"Kamu mungkin menyadari bahwa nilai kesehatan robot bisa turun di bawah "
"[code]0[/code]. Kita akan mempelajari cara menangani hal ini di pelajaran"
" selanjutnya dengan menggunakan [i]kondisi[/i]."

#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:61
msgid ""
"The robot's health could increase instead if the player picks up an item "
"that heals them, or if they use a healing item."
msgstr ""
"Kesehatan robot bisa meningkat jika pemain mengambil item yang "
"menyembuhkan, atau jika mereka menggunakan item penyembuh."

#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:81
msgid "Here again, the health can go beyond [code]100[/code]."
msgstr "Di sini juga, kesehatan bisa melebihi [code]100[/code]."

msgid ""
"Also, once more, the short line [code]health += amount[/code] is "
"equivalent to the longer form [code]health = health + amount[/code]."
msgstr ""
"Selain itu, sekali lagi, baris pendek [code]health += amount[/code] "
"setara dengan bentuk yang lebih panjang [code]health = health + "
"amount[/code]."

#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:91
msgid "Which of these would increase the health of the robot?"
msgstr "Manakah dari ini yang akan meningkatkan kesehatan robot?"

#: course/lesson-9-adding-and-subtracting/lesson.tres:94
msgid ""
"Both of these lines increase the [code]health[/code] of the robot by "
"[code]amount[/code].\n"
"[code]\n"
"health += amount\n"
"health = health + amount\n"
"[/code]"
msgstr ""
"Keduanya akan meningkatkan [code]health[/code] dari robot sebesar "
"[code]amount[/code].\n"
"[code]\n"
"health += amount\n"
"health = health + amount\n"
"[/code]"

